      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ bot Garden ¶ 19/[5]/7[2] ¶ The year appears tobe'73', but this is inconsistent with the comments about the groups of plants that M anticipates that Bentham will next need. He sent the last...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.05.19</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>f. 93.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">19/[5]/7[2]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The year appears to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'73', but this is inconsistent with the comments about the groups of plants that M anticipates that Bentham will next need. He sent the last of his supplemental Euphorbiaceae on 30 January 1973, and the main collection of Orchids on 23 August<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1872 (Notebook recording despatch of plants for Flora Australiensis,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>RB, MSS<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M44,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Library, Royal Botanic Gardens<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Melbourne). Bentham described his progress on Compositeae in G. Bentham to M, 25 January 1872<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 72-01-25a).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am always delighted, dear Mr Bentham, to see your handwriting and to read your kind and instructive letters. Let me thank you for all your sympathy.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>There is a reaction in my favor, and I have a fair prospect of surmounting all my difficulties. It is through an individual, and a very low one too, in the employ now of the Argus (Mr Edw Wilson's and Mr M'Kinnon's<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Lauchlan Mackinnon.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>paper) that my miseries and the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>desorganisation<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of my Department have been mainly brought about. The necessity of defending my Directorship has thrown almost all scientific work of mine during the last 18 month in the background.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A lot of Supplemental<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Euphorbiaceae ought to go to you within the next few months, so also other supplemental Monochlamydeae. I must then be guided by your wishes in further sendings, but expect that you need Orchideae first after that, unless - to keep Dicotyledoneae together - you prefer to supplement Thalamiflorae &amp;c in the volume, at least as far as new species are concerned.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is perfectly edifying to hear you speak of finishing the Compositae for the genera.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>What a treasure of information for all time that will be! The genera are far more important<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>then<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Austr. flora. Your new arrangement seems to simplify the distribution of Compositae in tribes &amp; subtribes much.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always yours<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>with deep reverence<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Compositae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Euphorbiaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Monochlamydeae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Orchideae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Thalamiflorae</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
